SWYFT DESKTOP - RESEARCH LOG (ANDROID LAUNCHER CORE)
Date: Development Day 2-3 Session
Platform: Android (Kotlin, AppCompatActivity)
Status: Working prototype launcher with grid UI

------------------------------------------------------------
1. PROJECT OVERVIEW
------------------------------------------------------------

Swyft Desktop is a hybrid system designed to:

- Turn an Android phone into a desktop-style environment
- Provide a grid-based app launcher similar to desktop OS design
- Eventually connect to a PC client for remote desktop interaction
- Maintain phone usability while providing a separate “desktop layer”

Current focus:
- Mobile launcher system (fully working)
- App listing + launching system
- UI grid layout with icons and labels

Future systems (not implemented yet):
- PC desktop environment (Windows client)
- Phone-as-input device (trackpad/keyboard mode)
- Remote app launching / sync system

------------------------------------------------------------
2. CURRENT IMPLEMENTATION SUMMARY
------------------------------------------------------------

WORKING FEATURES:

- Full app list retrieval using PackageManager
- Filtering launchable apps using ACTION_MAIN + CATEGORY_LAUNCHER
- Alphabetical sorting of apps
- Grid-based UI using GridLayout
- Scrollable launcher using ScrollView
- App launching via package manager intent
- Icon + label rendering per app tile
- Responsive 4-column grid layout
- Fixed tile sizing for consistent UI
- Proper text truncation (no overflow issues)
- Clean icon scaling system

------------------------------------------------------------
3. APP RETRIEVAL SYSTEM
------------------------------------------------------------

Apps are retrieved using Android PackageManager:

Intent filter used:
- ACTION_MAIN
- CATEGORY_LAUNCHER

This ensures only launchable apps appear in the launcher.

Result processing:
- ResolveInfo objects converted into AppInfo model
- AppInfo stores:
  - app name
  - package name
  - app icon drawable

Sorting:
- Alphabetical sorting applied using:
  name.lowercase()

Result:
- Stable, predictable app ordering in UI

------------------------------------------------------------
4. UI ARCHITECTURE
------------------------------------------------------------

LAYOUT STRUCTURE:

ScrollView
  └── GridLayout (columnCount = 4)
        └── App Tile (LinearLayout)
              ├── ImageButton (icon)
              └── TextView (label)

Design decisions:

- ScrollView used to handle large app lists
- GridLayout used for structured desktop-like layout
- Each app tile is a self-contained LinearLayout
- Icons and labels are vertically stacked

Tile behaviour:
- Fixed height (approx 220dp equivalent)
- Fixed icon size (approx 96px equivalent)
- Label constrained to single line with ellipsis

------------------------------------------------------------
5. TILE DESIGN SYSTEM
------------------------------------------------------------

Each app tile contains:

ICON:
- ImageButton
- Uses app system icon
- ScaleType: CENTER_CROP
- Transparent background
- Fixed size for consistency

LABEL:
- TextView under icon
- Font size: 12sp
- Max lines: 1
- Ellipsis applied for overflow

CONTAINER:
- LinearLayout (vertical)
- Center gravity alignment
- Padding applied for spacing
- Click area triggers app launch

------------------------------------------------------------
6. GRID SYSTEM BEHAVIOUR
------------------------------------------------------------

GridLayout configuration:

- 4 columns fixed
- Each tile width = 0 + weight distribution
- Uniform row height enforced
- ScrollView wraps entire grid

Result:
- Consistent desktop-style grid layout
- Predictable spacing between app tiles
- No overlap or clipping issues after fixes

------------------------------------------------------------
7. APP LAUNCH SYSTEM
------------------------------------------------------------

Launch method:

- Uses PackageManager.getLaunchIntentForPackage()
- Validates intent exists before launching
- Falls back with Toast error if app cannot launch

Behaviour:
- Opens apps in new task
- Does not interfere with launcher activity

------------------------------------------------------------
8. PROBLEMS ENCOUNTERED + RESOLUTIONS
------------------------------------------------------------

ISSUE 1: Only system apps appearing
CAUSE: Incorrect intent filtering
FIX: Ensured CATEGORY_LAUNCHER usage

ISSUE 2: App list incomplete
CAUSE: Improper query or missing launcher category
FIX: Fixed resolveInfo mapping

ISSUE 3: Grid not scrolling
CAUSE: Missing ScrollView wrapper
FIX: Wrapped GridLayout inside ScrollView

ISSUE 4: Icons too large / UI broken
CAUSE: No size constraints on ImageButton
FIX: Fixed icon size and container height

ISSUE 5: Text overflow
CAUSE: Labels not constrained
FIX: ellipsize + maxLines = 1

ISSUE 6: Layout instability
CAUSE: Missing layout params per tile
FIX: Explicit GridLayout.LayoutParams added

